{"key":"post-14379594","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14379594</id>\n<content>If you mist from day one, you're OK.&amp;nbsp; Some people don't mist at all, and then a week later when pins are dry and stunted, they mist heavily and screw things up.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't use a drip shield.&amp;nbsp; That was to prevent the huge drops that would rain down from the lids of the old style sealed up terrariums.&amp;nbsp; Those big drops would cause damage to the caps.&amp;nbsp; With a shotgun terrarium, you should never have condensation, so it's not a problem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mist enough to replace what has evaporated or been consumed by fruit production.</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>14379500</prev>\n<first>14379479</first>\n<last>14379594</last>\n<when>1304219456</when>\n<utime>05/01/11 06:10 AM</utime>\n</post>"}